summary: This is a domestic witness travel request form from an AUSA to the SDNY Victim/Witness Unit, dated November 20, 2021, for a fact witness in the case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell. The witness is scheduled to travel to the SDNY for trial preparation from November 27 to December 2, 2021.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell

persons.name: Ed Tyrrell
persons.context: Referenced in the form's instructions as a contact for guidance on witness travel funding for investigative interviews.

keyFacts: A fact witness was scheduled to travel to the SDNY for trial preparation in the Ghislaine Maxwell case from November 27 to December 2, 2021.
The witness was not a victim-witness, not facing criminal charges, and resided within the continental United States.
The document is a standardized DOJ form (rev. 2019.11.19) for domestic witness travel, indicating procedural handling of witnesses for the Maxwell trial.
The witness's identity is protected in this form, with fields for name, DOB, address, and contact information left blank in the provided text.
Instructions reference DOJ policies and Ed Tyrrell for guidance on funding different types of witness travel.
